-- Hunton & Williams Hires Ex-Milbank Partner for Corporate Team
-- B y   I a n   T h o m a s
-- 2012-02-07T20:49:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/hunton-williams-hires-ex-milbank-partner-for-corporate-team.html
Hunton & Williams LLP , a Richmond,
Virginia-based firm with more than 800 lawyers, hired John T. O’Connor, who was a partner at  Milbank, Tweed, Hadley & McCloy
LLP , as the firm expands its corporate practice.  O’Connor, 51, has experience in mergers and acquisitions,
private equity and securities matters, Hunton & Williams said
today in a statement. He will join the firm’s corporate practice
as a partner in its New York office.  “His significant M&A experience in the energy and
financial institution sectors complements the firm’s extensive
client base and presence in these two industries,” T. Justin Moore III, head of the corporate team, said in the statement.  Hunton & Williams was the 43rd-largest grossing law firm in
fiscal 2010 with revenue of $600 million,  according  to the
American Lawyer, a trade publication.  To contact the reporter on this story:
